/www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9039:"<div class="well content push-bottom">\n<h4>Note: <a href="https://appsumo.idevaffiliate.com/idevaffiliate.php?id=davidperel" target="_blank">Appsumo Launch Deal!</a></h4>\n<p>To celebrate the launch of Layers Pro 2, we are running an awesome deal with Appsumo. For only $39 you get Layers Pro 2, 4 themes and the Showcase portfolio plugin. <a href="https://www.appsumo.com/layerspro2/" target="_blank">Find out more here!</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>Late last year Marc and I took over full responsibility for live support. For a while we were responsible for every question and criticism that came our way.</p>\n<p>When we initially built Layers our philosophy was &#8220;less is more&#8221;.¬†Instead of loading the theme with features we kept it simple and as easy to use as possible and based on the feedback we have received from day 1 we achieved this goal.</p>\n<p>That being said, as more and more users have become familiar with Layers we realised the need to open up the scope for customizability.</p>\n<p>With our nose to the ground, deep in the support section, we came up with a list of priorities¬†for¬†the next version of Layers and came up with a plan.¬†The initial challenge was coming up with an interface that was still easy to use and understand while still unlocking the customizability many of your badly wanted.</p>\n<p>We have achieved this and are super proud to be releasing <a href="https://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro 2</a>¬†which features a new widget interface and much more customizability.</p>\n<h2>Layers Pro 2. More Power. More Control.</h2>\n<p>A bunch of new controls have been added to all the standard and Pro widgets in the latest version of Layers.</p>\n<h3>New Accordion Based Interface</h3>\n<p>Just as simple as before but with more power. The¬†new accordion based interface allows us to keep the overall design of our unique widgets while still making new controls available in just a few clicks.</p>\n<p>This has allowed us to add a number of options, including the ability for you to adjust button, tab and accordion¬†hover states and more.</p>\n<h3>Font Control</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-font-controls.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-13005" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-font-controls.png" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-font-controls.png 640w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-font-controls-300x225.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">For the first time ever in Layers you can now choose your fonts for each widget, slider and content block.¬†Options include:</span></p>\n<ol>\n<li class="p1">Color</li>\n<li class="p1">Font size, line height and letter spacing</li>\n<li class="p1">Font weights</li>\n<li class="p1">Font style and font case</li>\n</ol>\n<p>And pretty soon we will also provide you with the ability to choose¬†your font family!</p>\n<h3>Ability to¬†Add and Edit Borders</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-border-controls.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-13003" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-border-controls.png" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-border-controls.png 640w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-border-controls-300x225.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>\n<p>Adding borders to your widgets and content columns was a big feature that was missing from version 1 but that has changed with Layers Pro 2! You can now add borders on any side along with the ability to choose border style and ¬†border radius.</p>\n<h3>More Button Control</h3>\n<p>In Layers 1 it was possible to set the color and we&#8217;d automatically apply the font and hover colors. There were also 3 size settings that you could choose from: small, medium and large. Well now we&#8217;ve unlocked all the¬†available¬†options. Take a quick look at the new interface:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-button-options.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-13506" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-button-options-1024x850.png" alt="" width="1024" height="850" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-button-options-1024x850.png 1024w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-button-options-300x249.png 300w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-button-options-768x637.png 768w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-button-options.png 1070w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n<h4><strong>The new button settings include:</strong></h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Background color</li>\n<li>Borders (including thickness, style¬†and radius)</li>\n<li>Fonts¬†styling</li>\n<li>Shadows</li>\n<li>Padding and Margins</li>\n<li>For the first time in Layers you&#8217;ll also be able to choose hover styling as well.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Page and Widget Animations</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-animate-option.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-13048" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-animate-option.png" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-animate-option.png 640w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-new-animate-option-300x225.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>\n<p>Let your pages come to life with new widget and page load animations! There are two areas which you can now apply them:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>On Page Load</strong> &#8211; Any non-Layers builder page will now elegantly fade and blend¬†in during the loading phase.</li>\n<li><strong>Widgets</strong> &#8211; Now when scrolling down¬†any Layers page you will notice your widgets beautifully fade in and slide up.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We are excited to expand this feature in the future but area already incredibly happy with¬†the subtle effect this new feature has on the feeling of quality when visiting a Layers site.</p>\n<h3>Images and Background also have New Options</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-background-image-options.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-13687" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-background-image-options.png" alt="" width="640" height="510" srcset="https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-background-image-options.png 640w, https://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/layers-2-background-image-options-300x239.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>\n<p>New features in the background and image settings bring you the ability to do a number of cool new things:</p>\n<p><strong>Background Settings:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Background repeat</li>\n<li>Background position</li>\n<li>Improved settings interface</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Image Settings:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Image resizing (set max width and max height of your images)</li>\n<li>Image radius</li>\n<li>And finally, a new lightbox setting</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>What is Part¬†2?</h3>\n<p>You may have noticed that we mention &#8220;Part 1&#8221; in the headline and there&#8217;s good reason for that. Brand new widget controls are just the first step in a big update that we hope to release in a phased approach. Some of the stuff you can look forward to in the near future is:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Brand new header and footer customizability¬†controls</li>\n<li>The ability to edit your blog list and single post pages without touching a line of code</li>\n<li>Much deeper sidebar customizability options</li>\n<li>New widgets</li>\n</ol>\n<p>But for now we invite you to <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/update-layers/">download the latest version of Layers</a> and <a href="https://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro 2</a> and start enjoying our latest product.</p>\n<div class="well content">\n<h4>Note: <a href="https://www.appsumo.com/layerspro2/" target="_blank">Appsumo Launch Deal!</a></h4>\n<p>To celebrate the launch of Layers Pro 2, we are running an awesome deal with Appsumo. For only $39 you get Layers Pro 2, 4 themes and the Showcase portfolio plugin. <a href="https://appsumo.idevaffiliate.com/idevaffiliate.php?id=davidperel" target="_blank">Find out more here!</a>\n</div>\n<p><em>If you already purchased Layers Pro, the update to <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-update-layers-pro/">Layers Pro 2 is free</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.layerswp.com/2017/05/introducing-layers-pro-2-part-one/">Introducing Layers Pro 2. Part One.</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"https://www.layerswp.com/2017/05/introducing-layers-pro-2-part-one/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"